## What this is

`<PROJECT_NAME>` (`<PROJECT_NAME_LOCALIZED>`) — `<one-line description, e.g. a full-stack web app for the X assessment/workflow>`. .NET 10 Clean Architecture backend + Next.js 16 frontend + Expo mobile, SQL Server, MinIO (S3), `<primary-language/RTL note if any>`. The interactive domain logic lives in a shared TypeScript package both clients import; the backend is the system of record.

## Commands

### Backend (.NET 10, solution `<PROJECT_NAME>.slnx`)
```bash
docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.dev.yml up -d   # SQL Server (sa) + MinIO (minioadmin) — needed to run the API
dotnet build <PROJECT_NAME>.slnx                        # build all
dotnet run --project src/Web                            # API on http://localhost:5000  (Scalar docs at /scalar)
dotnet test                                             # all tests
dotnet test tests/Domain.UnitTests/Domain.UnitTests.csproj   # one project
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~<SomeTests>"        # one test/class
```
Build output goes to `./artifacts/` (not `bin/obj`, via `ArtifactsPath` in `Directory.Build.props`).

EF Core migrations (the `dotnet-ef` global tool MUST match EF Core 10 — `dotnet tool update -g dotnet-ef --version "10.0.*"`):
```bash
dotnet ef migrations add <Name> --project src/Infrastructure --startup-project src/Web --output-dir Data/Migrations
```
Migrations are applied automatically on API startup (every environment) by `ApplicationDbContextInitialiser`, which also seeds the `Administrator`/`User` roles and an admin user from `AdminUser:Email`/`AdminUser:Password` config.

### Frontend (`web/`, Next.js 16)
```bash
cd web && npm install
npm run dev      # http://localhost:3000
npm run build    # production build (must pass before deploy)
npm run lint
```
`web/.env.local` sets `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE` (dev `http://localhost:5000`). This is baked at build time. `next.config.ts` must keep `output: "standalone"` for the Docker image, and `transpilePackages: ["@<SCOPE>/<CORE_PACKAGE>"]` so the shared package compiles.

### Mobile (`mobile/`, Expo SDK 54)
```bash
cd mobile
npm run start      # Metro dev server (Expo Go / dev client)
npm run android    # expo run:android (needs Android SDK)
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
```
API base resolves `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE` -> `app.json extra.apiBase` -> a production fallback. Metro is configured (`metro.config.js`) to resolve `@<SCOPE>/<CORE_PACKAGE>` from the monorepo root.

### Shared package & install
```bash
npm install                                   # repo root — npm workspaces hoists web/mobile/packages
npm test -w packages/<CORE_PACKAGE>           # Vitest, asserts numeric parity of the domain engine
```

## Architecture

### Backend layering (`src/`, from the Jason Taylor Clean Architecture template + .NET Aspire)
- **Domain** — entities (`<Entity1>`, `<Entity2>`, `Subscription`, `<ReportEntity>`) and the domain calculators in `Domain/Services`: `<Calculator1>` and `<ReferenceData>`. **These are faithful ports of the legacy logic — keep them numerically identical to the shared TS package; they're covered by unit tests.**
- **Application** — CQRS use cases (MediatR), FluentValidation validators, AutoMapper profiles (defined as nested `Mapping : Profile` classes inside DTOs). Service contracts live in `Application/Common/Interfaces`.
- **Infrastructure** — EF Core + **Microsoft SQL Server**, ASP.NET Identity, and the implementations: `MinioFileStorage` (IFileStorage), `QuestPdfReportGenerator` (IReportGenerator), `SubscriptionService`, `UserAdminService`, `OtpService`/`SmsSender`, `GoogleTokenValidator`, `<ExternalProviderImpl>`.
- **Web** — Minimal-API endpoints. Each `IEndpointGroup` class is auto-mapped at **`/api/{ClassName}`**. Identity API is mounted via `MapIdentityApi` under `/api/Users/*` (bearer tokens). The DI extension lives in `Infrastructure/DependencyInjection.cs` -> `Add<PROJECT_NAME>Services`.

### Key architectural decision: where the domain logic lives
The interactive **<domain engine, e.g. N-checklist scoring>** runs in the **FRONTEND**, in the shared package **`@<SCOPE>/<CORE_PACKAGE>`** (`packages/<CORE_PACKAGE>/`, pure TypeScript, no framework deps), so web and mobile compute identical results. The **backend is the system of record**: `<MainEntity>.InputJson`/`ResultJson` are stored as SQL Server **`nvarchar(max)`** plus denormalised `TotalScore`/`MaxScore`, and the PDF is generated from the stored result. So changes to the domain logic/inputs go in **`packages/<CORE_PACKAGE>/src/*`**, **not** the backend. (The `Domain/Services` calculators are a parallel port kept numerically in sync, locked by tests.)

### Auth & roles
- Three sign-in methods: username/password (Identity API), **mobile OTP** (`/api/Auth/otp/*`), **Google ID-token** (`/api/Auth/google`). The OTP/Google flows in `Web/Endpoints/Auth.cs` issue Identity bearer tokens by setting `signInManager.AuthenticationScheme = IdentityConstants.BearerScheme` then `SignInAsync`.
- Roles: **`Administrator`** (manage users + subscriptions) and **`User`** (default). `/api/Admin/*` is gated with `RequireRole(Administrator)`; `GET /api/Users/me` returns `{ roles, isAdmin }`.
- **Subscriptions** cap projects per user (Free = **<FREE_QUOTA, e.g. 5>** by default), enforced in `ISubscriptionService.EnsureCanCreateProjectAsync` (throws a `ValidationException` surfaced under the `Subscription` field).

### Frontend structure (`web/src`)
- Next.js App Router under `app/[locale]`. **i18n via next-intl**: `<PRIMARY_LOCALE>` (default, **<RTL/LTR>**) + `<SECONDARY_LOCALE>`, `localePrefix: "as-needed"` -> the default locale is served at `/`, the other at `/<code>/...`. The real `<html lang/dir>` + providers are in `app/[locale]/layout.tsx`.
- Route groups: **root `/` = public landing page** (`components/landing/*`); `(auth)` = public login/register; `(dashboard)` = protected by `<RequireAuth>` and includes the admin area (`admin/users`, shown only when `useAuth().isAdmin`).
- **Design system**: shadcn-style CSS variable tokens in `app/globals.css` (`<ACCENT, e.g. emerald>` primary) with light/dark via `components/theme-provider.tsx`. Shared UI primitives in `components/ui` — **keep its export surface stable (restyle, don't rename)** since every page imports from it.
- API layer in `lib/`: `api.ts` (fetch wrapper with bearer + auto-refresh), `endpoints.ts` (`authApi`/`projectsApi`/`subscriptionApi`/`adminApi`), `auth-context.tsx` (`useAuth` exposing `user`/`isAdmin`), `tokens.ts` (localStorage). Use locale-aware `Link`/`useRouter` from `@/i18n/navigation`, not `next/link`.

### Mobile structure (`mobile/`)
- Expo SDK 54 with **expo-router** (file-based nav). Default locale `<PRIMARY_LOCALE>`; RTL forced via `I18nManager.forceRTL(true)` in the root layout if the primary language is RTL.
- Tokens stored with **expo-secure-store** (OS keystore), not localStorage. `apiFetch` does a one-shot 401 retry against `/api/Users/refresh`.
- Imports the same `@<SCOPE>/<CORE_PACKAGE>` functions as web, so mobile results match exactly.

## Gotchas

- **Build is strict**: `TreatWarningsAsErrors=true`. NuGet-audit advisories on transitive template packages (`OpenTelemetry`, `System.Security.Cryptography.Xml`) are demoted to warnings via `WarningsNotAsErrors` (`NU1608;NU1902;NU1903`) in `Directory.Build.props`. `.NET 10` also turns deprecations into errors (e.g. use `KnownIPNetworks`, not `KnownNetworks`).
- **`ValidationException` is ambiguous** between `FluentValidation.ValidationException` (a global using) and the app's `Application.Common.Exceptions.ValidationException` — alias the app one when using it.
- **Aspire namespace clash**: a `<PROJECT_NAME>.Application.<Feature>` namespace can shadow Aspire's generated global `<Feature>` namespace in functional tests — qualify the generated one as `global::<Feature>.TestAppHost`.
- **MediatR v14** requires a commercial license for production (logs a dev-only warning); replace or license before going live.
- Use `Guard.Against.NotFound(...)` (Ardalis) for 404s; `ForbiddenAccessException` -> 403 (see `ProblemDetailsExceptionHandler`).
- **Keep large JSON as `nvarchar(max)`** (provider-portable text), not a SQL JSON column type — so swapping the DB provider needs no entity-mapping change.

## Deployment (`deploy/`)

- `docker-compose.dev.yml` — local SQL Server + MinIO only. `docker-compose.local.yml` — full stack in containers. `docker-compose.server.yml` — production, **attaches to the server's existing Traefik** (external network `<TRAEFIK_NETWORK>`, cert resolver `<CERT_RESOLVER>`) instead of running its own.
- **Live**: `<WEB_DOMAIN>` (web), `<API_DOMAIN>`, `<S3_DOMAIN>`, on server `<SERVER_IP>` under `<SERVER_PATH>`.
- If the server's network blocks the base-image registry (e.g. `mcr.microsoft.com` and the Docker Hub blob CDN): build the `api`/`web` images where the registry works, `docker save | gzip` -> transfer -> `docker load`; pull `minio`/other backing images via the **`<REGISTRY_MIRROR>`** mirror (referenced directly in `docker-compose.server.yml`). **Do not restart a shared Docker daemon** if it runs other production stacks.
- SSH/transfer may use PuTTY `plink`/`pscp -pw` (no `sshpass`). In production MinIO is reached via its public host (`Minio__Endpoint=<S3_DOMAIN>`, `UseSSL=true`) so presigned report URLs are valid for browsers.
